Defendant Eric D Butler in court with attorney Leah R. Thomas.  Defendant Eric D Butler in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 1 YEAR in the House of Correction with credit for 78 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.
Conditions: 
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Mental health assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Letter of apology to Byron C. (Pick and Save);
*  Seek/maintain full time employment;
*  Court will waive any costs and surcharges that can be waived.  Pay costs and surcharges that can not be waived or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
